#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "Compressing native executables using UPX"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid ""
"https://upx.github.io/[Ultimate Packer for eXecutables (UPX)] is a compression tool reducing the size of executables.\n"
"Quarkus can compress the produced native executable to reduce its size.\n"
"Such compression is interesting when:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "building CLI tools, and you want to reduce the disk footprint,"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "building small container images."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "Note that UPX compression:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "increases your build time, mainly if you use high-compression levels"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "increases the startup RSS usage of the application"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "System vs. Container"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "The UPX compression requires:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "the `upx` command to be available in the system `PATH`;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "an explicitly defined `quarkus.native.compression.container-image`;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "or to have built the native executable using an in-container build."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "If `quarkus.native.compression.container-image` is not set explicitly, it will implicitly default to `quarkus.native.builder-image`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid ""
"If you have the `upx` command available on your path, Quarkus uses it.\n"
"Otherwise, if you built the native image using an in-container build (using `quarkus.native.container-build=true`) and if the compression image provides the `upx` command, Quarkus compresses the executable from inside the container."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "If you want to force compression to take place in a container, you can set `quarkus.native.compression.container-build` to `true` (or `false` to explicitly not run compression in a container)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "If you are not in one of these cases, the compression fails."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid ""
"Setting `quarkus.native.compression.container-image` results in the compression to run in a container.\n"
"If you want to set the variable, but not run the compression in a container, set `quarkus.native.compression.container-build` explicitly to `false`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "`WORKDIR` for the image used for compression"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid ""
"The executable to compress is mounted in directory `/project`.\n"
"Since the container runs `upx` in the current working directory, the `WORKDIR` of the image used for compression must be `/project`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "Compression can be explicitly en-/disabled by setting `quarkus.native.compression.enabled`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "upx is cross-platform."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "`upx` can compress executables using a different architecture and OS than your host machine. For example, `upx` on a macOS machine can compress a Linux 64-bits executables."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "Configuring the UPX compression"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "Then, in your application configuration, enable the compression by configuring the _compression level_ you want:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid ""
"If the compression level is not set, the compression is disabled.\n"
"The compression will happen once the native executable is built and will replace the executable."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "Compression level"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "The compression level goes from 1 to 10:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "`1`: faster compression"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "`9`: better compression"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "`10`: best compression (can be slow for big files)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "Extra parameters"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid ""
"You can pass extra parameter to upx, such as `--brute` or `--ultra-brute` using the `quarkus.native.compression.additional-args` parameter.\n"
"The value is a comma-separated list of arguments:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/upx.adoc
msgid "The exhaustive list of parameters can be found in https://github.com/upx/upx/blob/devel/doc/upx.pod[the UPX documentation]."
msgstr ""
